  "elapsed_s": 7.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I was the Portuguese consul in Bordeaux, France and I was expelled by the Portuguese government from my position because I issued visas to all these people against the orders of the Portuguese Prime Minister Salazar, Antonio de Oliveira Salazar.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I still couldn't quite understand exactly why should a man of such a stature be expelled because he gave visas?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He was saving lives.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "The Portuguese government should be honored to have such a man on their team.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But that was not the case and Dr. de Sousa Mendes actually was-- had received orders from the ambassador of Portugal in London, England at some point in time in the '40s- 1940, perhaps 1941-- not to issue visas to Jews or to members of communities with impure blood-- I believe it was also referring to gypsies-- and not to members of the anti-German movement, if you wish, anti-Nazis, and also not to issue visas to members of some other countries that had been overrun by the Nazis, if it was Belgian or Holland or France or et cetera.",
      "word_count": 99
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So as a result, Dr. de Sousa Mendes-- he-- he said of very famous words that was told later on by his son to me, that I'd rather be on the side of God against man, as opposed to being on the side of man against God.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And his conscience, as he said, did not allow him to allow so many people to die simply because they were Jews.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And outside the Portuguese Consul in Bordeaux, France, there were hundreds-- hundreds-- of refugees waiting to receive that piece of paper.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
